{"article_id":"ml6fBfBWQflibm4n","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"In the weeks","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"following Trump ' s election ,","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"as elites tried to make sense of what went so horribly wrong","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"( as they saw it ) ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"many an accusing eye turned its gaze toward Facebook .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"There were now-familiar criticisms of the social network site","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"- notably that it places us into echo-chambers ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"feeding us stories","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"that reinforce our political views .","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"But a new scourge also emerged :","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"Facebook ,","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"according to reports from BuzzFeed and other sources ,","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"had become a breeding ground for misinformation and purposeful disinformation .","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"The rise of fake news on Facebook is worrisome ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"to be sure .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"And to their credit , Facebook executives took the issue seriously","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"and introduced a system","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"through which articles","depth":13},{"id":18,"text":"flagged by users","depth":13},{"id":19,"text":"will be vetted by fact-checkers","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"- a welcome , if far from perfect , development .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"But there is an equally worrisome risk","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"as we jump to fix the fake news problem ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"we may end up destroying our best hope","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"to break through our echo chambers .","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"That hope is , contrary to much of what you ' ve read ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"Facebook itself .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"Yes , contrary to common belief , Facebook and other social media sites may not be the fomenters of hyper-polarization","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"often thought ;","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"they could , in fact , be a powerful force","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"that pushes us out of our ideological silos .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"Some of the evidence","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"that social media serves more as a bridge than a divider","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"comes from studies","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"that ,","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"as it happens ,","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"set out to make the case","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"that social media split us into political bubbles .","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"But those bubbles ,","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"it turns out ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"are far from airtight .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"Something from 15 percent to 25 percent of the people","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"we connect to on social media ,","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"on average , come from across the political divide .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Those numbers might seem small ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"but they are at least comparable to the level of diversity","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"we come across in real life .","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"( According to the 2008 American National Election Survey ,","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"20 percent of the partisans","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"Democrats spoke to about politics","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"were Republican","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"and 22 percent of Republicans ' political interlocutors were Democratic . )","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"And there are reasons","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"to suspect","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"that our online networks might be more productively diverse than our real-life circles .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"When it comes to our daily lives ,","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"homophily","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"- the tendency","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"to surround ourselves with like-minded people -","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"is a strong force .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"But homophily is weaker among our more distant connections , those people","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"whom we see rarely .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"And this is where Facebook comes in :","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"The social network has proven especially good at facilitating connections with our second- and third-tier friends .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"People","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"we rarely , if ever , schedule social events with offline","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"nonetheless hover perceptively in the margins of our online social networks .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"And social media may not only increase the odds","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"we connect to someone on the other side of political spectrum","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"- extending a \" friend \" request ,","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"accepting one -","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"but also that we share our views with them .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"Etiquette and our instinct","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"to avoid conflict","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"keep us from bringing up politics at the dinner table or around the water cooler .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"For better or worse , those rules of decorum get tossed out online .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"Research confirms","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"that that the diversity of our online networks ,","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"combined with our relative disinhibition online ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"indeed exposes us to views","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"we wouldn ' t otherwise come across","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"- and may even lead us to moderate some of our more extreme views .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"When Facebook researchers examined the diversity of their users ' networks in 2015 ,","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"they found","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"- echoing the studies","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"mentioned above -","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"that on average our bubbles are quite porous :","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"18 percent of self-described liberals ' connections were conservative","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"and 20 percent of self-described conservatives ' friends were liberal .","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"More surprisingly , those connections delivered to the social network ' s users a diverse set of political news :","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"24 percent of the news items","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"liberals saw","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"were conservative-leaning","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"and 38 percent of the news","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"conservatives saw","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"was liberal-leaning .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"And we might not just be seeing those diverse stories on our feed ;","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"research by the computational statistician Seth Flaxman and colleagues suggests","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"we may be clicking on them as well .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"Flaxman tracked the web-surfing behavior of 50,000 internet users","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"and compared the diversity of news","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"they read -","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"taking note of whether these news consumers arrived at sites via a news aggregator ,","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"using a search tool ,","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"directly accessing a news site , or through social media .","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"News aggregators and search sites had the best bubble-bursting record :","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"They led internet users to the widest array of stories and to the most stories","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"that challenged users ' political views .","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"Social media trailed aggregators and search on this measure ;","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"still , people","depth":15},{"id":111,"text":"who relied on social media for news","depth":15},{"id":112,"text":"got more diverse and challenging information","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"than did the people","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"who navigated directly to their favorite news sites .","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"Exposed to different points of view ,","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"people changed their news-consumption habits","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"That exposure to diverse news might even turn out to be a moderating force .","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"Pablo Barbera looked at the political leanings and networks of Twitter users from 2013 to 2014 .","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"He not only found","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"- again , echoing other studies -","depth":15},{"id":121,"text":"that users had remarkable diversity in their friends :","depth":15},{"id":122,"text":"For half of all users , at least 30 percent of friends did not share their ideology .","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"He also found","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"that users","depth":16},{"id":125,"text":"whose online friend circles included at least 20 percent","depth":17},{"id":126,"text":"who disagreed with them","depth":17},{"id":127,"text":"became more centrist over time ,","depth":15},{"id":128,"text":"as measured by the news sources","depth":15},{"id":129,"text":"they followed .","depth":15},{"id":130,"text":"To be sure ,","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"neither Facebook nor Twitter represents the ideal of a \" public sphere. \"","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"As anyone","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"who has de-friended a particularly offensive acquaintance ,","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"or simply taken a Facebook mental health break ,","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"will attest ,","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"Facebook exchanges can often feel more like cage-fighting than Socratic dialogue .","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"Not all dialogue is productive dialogue ,","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"researchers tell us :","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"Without a foundation of respect , for example , discussion with a political opponent may make us dig our heels in","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"- and convince us","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"that our political foes are as ignorant and evil","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"as we always knew them to be .","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"That , indeed , may be the true issue with social media","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"- not that it seals us off from opposing views ,","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"but that it exposes us to the worst in political dialogue :","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"to heated ad-hominem attacks , cherry-picked evidence and ,","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"as we ' ve seen in recent weeks ,","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"false information .","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"Those polarizing forces need to be tempered ,","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"but","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"as we confront that problem","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"we should be careful not to accidentally dismantle the bridge","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"social media offers .","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"Consider the recent offensive against fake news .","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"As others have noted ,","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"the primary risk of \" fake story \" fixes and other attempts","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"to regulate Facebook","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"is that they will be perceived as biased","depth":15},{"id":159,"text":"( or , worse , be biased )","depth":15},{"id":160,"text":"toward one side of the political divide .","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"Such a perception could have the backfiring effect","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"of making users on the extremes flee the network","depth":15},{"id":163,"text":"-","depth":15},{"id":164,"text":"perhaps to read alternative media ,","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"effectively sealing themselves off from opposing viewpoints .","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"Then we will , indeed , have airtight echo chambers on social media .","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"One way","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"to avoid the appearance of bias","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"is to make any fake-news detector","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"( or other de-polarizing tool )","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"optional","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"- preferably \" opt-in \" rather than \" opt-out , \"","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"so users feel truly empowered","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"in creating their online environment .","depth":10},{"id":175,"text":"To help encourage the adoption of those tools ,","depth":9},{"id":176,"text":"Facebook could provide nudges","depth":10},{"id":177,"text":"by posting notices","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"when one ' s friends turn on a fake-news-evaluation app .","depth":11},{"id":179,"text":"This bruising election season has left some Americans understandably doubtful","depth":5},{"id":180,"text":"that social media can be force for democratic good ,","depth":5},{"id":181,"text":"but we can ' t give up hope .","depth":4},{"id":182,"text":"That ' s not just because social media is likely to increasingly be our gateway to political information ,","depth":4},{"id":183,"text":"but because ,","depth":5},{"id":184,"text":"contrary to conventional wisdom , it still holds considerable potential","depth":6},{"id":185,"text":"to bridge our divides .","depth":6},{"id":186,"text":"Julia Kamin is a PhD candidate in the department of political science at the University of Michigan .","depth":1}],"relations":[{"parent":373,"left":372,"right":186,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":372,"left":365,"right":371,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":365,"left":239,"right":364,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":239,"left":214,"right":238,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"left":191,"right":213,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":191,"left":190,"right":4,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":190,"left":188,"r